<br>
<br>
Rhasin: - Magician Burnout 4 buff bug:<br>
<br>
I think I sent this in already, but Burnout 4 now seems to give 55 charisma to our pets, and no AC anymore. I figure this is a typo, but if you could look into it, it'd be great.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Alan: I heard nothing about a change to BO4.  I'll ask about it, but my suspicion here is that someone's assuming more than they should about the spdat file...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Rhasin: It was my assumption/understanding that the spdat file was no longer in use. That set of spell data has 'drifted' out of alignment with current spell effects, and not only that, with spell changes, that file is no longer updated via the patcher (a good indication it's a now inert file). <br>
<br>
I *think* (could not say for certainty) that the AC components of Burnout (1-4) were being adjusted because Burnout no longer stacked with the Post-50 fire pets new self buff 'Shielding' (also uses a AC value in slot 2). AC values for Burnout were being moved to slot 6, so that we could at least self-haste our fire pets without overwriting their 'Shielding' buff (or not hasting them at all, if you did not have Burnout 4, the first pet buff in the series capable of overwriting Shielding). <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Arch Mage<BR>
